'''Rodiya''' is a [[dialect]] of the [[Sinhalese language]] spoken by members of the [[Rodiya]] community of [[Sri Lanka]]. Speakers are considered to be low-[[Indian caste system|caste]] among the [[Sinhalese people]].

Examples of Rodiya words:<ref>Gunasekara, ''A comprehensive grammar of the Sinhalese language'' (1891), pag. 384</ref>
*'''dissenavā''' ''to come'' (Sinhala '''enavā''')
*'''dumana''' ''house'' (Sinhala '''geya, gedara''')
*'''galla''' ''mouth'' (Sinhala '''kaṭa''')
*'''gävā''' ''man'' (Sinhala '''minihā''')
*'''gävī''' ''woman'' (Sinhala '''gäänu''')
*'''miganavā''' ''to eat'' (Sinhala '''kanavā''')

